name: Peace & Beauty Blend in Valldemossa
summary: Located just outside the village of Valldemossa high up in the Tramuntana mountain range, this charming villa offers a wonderful combination of tranquillity and beauty. Valldemossa is the highest village in Mallorca, and without a doubt one of the prettiest.
space: Built in a traditional Mallorquin style, this large stone villa offers guests the perfect combination of the classic and the contemporary. Set in spacious private grounds with wonderful views of the surrounding countryside, the property offers a high level of peace and privacy. The outdoor space is one of the real highlights, and includes a modern pool with sun-deck, chill-out and dining area, manicured lawns and even its own large pond. An abundance of local flora provide natural respite from the bright sun during the summer months. Beautifully decorated and furnished with traditional Mallorquin pieces throughout, the house is bright, light and elegant. Exposed ceiling beams, flagstone tiles, marble flooring, and classic wooden window shutters all combine to create a space that is both stylish and comfortable. At Villa Club we aim to provide the very best in hospitality and service throughout Spain. We warmly welcome you to stay at one of our beautiful Villas and invite you to relax pool side or to enjoy some of the best foods and sights that Spain has to offer.

Each Villa offers a comfortable and welcoming home away from home in some of the most sought after locations in the Balearic Islands, Andalusia and Catalonia. Each Villa comes fully-equipped with everything you may need during for you to enjoy your holidays.

We have Villas to suit everyone’s tastes including modern seaside homes and historic residences in the Spanish countryside.

Please contact us if you require further info about our villas, we are always happy to help!

name: 2bdr flat in the heart of Edinburgh
summary: You will love the huge, bright bedrooms and living room, the cozy kitchen and the refurbished bathroom!  And of course that lovely wee park at the other side of the road! Close to major train stations and roads and a 7min walk from the city centre! Enjoy! :)

description: You will love the huge, bright bedrooms and living room, the cozy kitchen and the refurbished bathroom!  And of course that lovely wee park at the other side of the road! Close to major train stations and roads and a 7min walk from the city centre! Enjoy! :) Victorian style 2 bedrooom flat with high ceilings and views to the park across the street and the private garden at the back! Two huge and bright double bedrooms, with a separate living room, hall and kitchen!! And of course the newly renovated bathroom! :) Only a 5min walk from the Haymarket station (Buses and trams to airport and trains to Glasgow), 4min walk to Lothian Road (one of the busiest roads in Edinburgh) and a 7min walk from Princes street (city centre). What’s there to see? 1.Sightseeing i.The Dungeons - £10 for a guided tour (I think, not sure) ii.Royal Mile iii.Edinburgh Castle - £15 iv.Calton Hill  v.The Meadows vi.Holyrood Park vii.Old College viii.The Union Canal (great walks and even greater cycling flat route r
notes: What’s there to see? 1.Sightseeing i.The Dungeons - £10 for a guided tour (I think, not sure) ii.Royal Mile iii.Edinburgh Castle - £15 iv.Calton Hill  v.The Meadows vi.Holyrood Park vii.Old College viii.The Union Canal (great walks and even greater cycling flat route reaching Glasgow!!!) ix.The Botanical Gardens (magnificent – especially in spring summer) x.Water of Leith (great walk) Where to eat? 1.Anywhere on Grassmarket Only half a mile to the east you can visit the famous Grassmarket; ideal for a pint or dinner. Really love the Petit Paris restaurant, Steak and Mussels the Italian restaurants (especially the pizza one) 2.Victoria street Oink is the most famous spot for hog roast; good quantity and perfect for a quick bite, located on the street from where Diagon Alley was inspired 3.Rose street Busy street, full of pubs and restaurants Meze meze is my favourite restaurant in Edinburgh; comparatively low prices and (really) good quantity, along with authentic flavours from the Medi
transit: Only a 5min walk from the Haymarket station (Buses and trams to airport and trains to Glasgow), 4min walk to Lothian Road (one of the busiest roads in Edinburgh) and a 7min walk from Princes street (city centre).
access: Two huge and bright double bedrooms, with a separate living room, hall and kitchen!! And of course the newly renovated bathroom! :)
host_about:
A (relatively) young, energetic person from Cyprus eager for new experiences and to meet new people!!! I live in Edinburgh for almost 5 years now and can confirm that if there is a place to visit in the UK, well drop by and you will never regret it!!! :)

As for me; apart from my daily lame routine that involves working from 9 to 5:30 every week day, I tend to go for the occasional run, some cycling and generally, anything that gets me out of the house after work. But what i love and enjoy the most is nothing else but dancing!!! So if you want to dance your night away in Edinburgh, you are more than welcome to my flat!! :)

I 've used Airbnb before, when i traveled to the US and I loved the idea; I always believed that people are awesome and Airbnb is here to prove that!! :)

Many thanks and see you soon!!
Demos
street: Gardner's Crescent, Edinburgh, City of Edinburgh EH3, United Kingdom

The famous Hollywood Boulevard is only a 3 stop train ride away, about 10min. You can easily take a walk there as well which will take you about 30min. Public transportation is all in walking distance and there are plenty of grocery stores and small food places around. In about 15min walking distance you will be on Vermont Avenue with a lot of nice restaurants and shopping possibilities. One of my favorite stores is the Vintage store Squaresville which is pretty popular for it's amazing selection of Vintage clothing.

space: Built with careful attention paid to every detail this villa is the perfect place for a family to set up base for the summer. From the house you have fantastic views of the bay of Palma and the sea. The house is open plan with a large fully equipped kitchen and sitting room area on the ground floor. The enormous glass doors open fully onto a terrace area allowing the outside and inside of the house to become one large space to enjoy the wonderful Mallorca sunshine. Upstairs there are three double bedrooms, each one with their own bathroom and the master bedroom with a bath and shower suite as well as a projector. Once again the large glass windows slide open allowing in a cool sea breeze on warm summer nights. The house benefits from a service suite and a large garage with space for 3 cars. Es Raconer offers guests a haven just outside Palma that is close to the beach and offers a truly luxurious stay.

Upstairs there are 3 double rooms and a bathroom. Over the years the house has seen seen several renorvations but always sympathetically and tastefully carried out in keeping with the historic character of the dwelling. Finca Sa Tafona is located in a privileged setting surrounded by low green hills in quiet countryside. There is a large private swimming pool equipped with deckchairs and parasols, from where you can enjoy  beautiful panoramic views of San Salva

space: The front bedroom downstairs near the front door and half bathroom.  Kitchen is down the hall as well as a laundry closet and a full bathroom with clawfoot tub and handheld shower head.  It's a beautiful house with high ceilings, crown molding, and exposed century-old brick chimneys! Your room also has large picture windows, and a great carved wooden mantel.  A nice large desk is available for any working travelers! The kitchen is fully equipped: gas range with cast iron griddle, dual gas oven, microwave oven, and a modern fridge/freezer.  Cookware, utensils, and dishes are available.  There is a modern nice washer and dryer for your use in the laundry room on the side of the kitchen.  We have two sweet tuxedo cats that mostly stay outdoors but occasionally run inside, and we adopted a super sweet, dorky puppy that mostly stays upstairs with me or in the backyard. neighborhood_overview: The house is a comfortable 1 mile walk across the scenic Shelby Street pedestrian bridge to downtown and less than a mile to Five Points, the heart of the East Nashville business district featuring 3 Crow Bar, The 5 Spot, and Margot Cafe.  Even closer are Sky Blue Cafe for a great local breakfast or good coffee, and The Crying Wolf, a hip new bar with great simple cocktails and amazing burgers.
notes: We have two tuxedo cats and a puppy, they're very sweet and really not a problem for anyone with MILD allergies since they mostly stay outside or upstairs with me. Also, we allow guests with pets to stay as long as they play nice!  The house is very clean, however probably not the best choice for anyone with severe cat or dog allergies.
transit: There is a bus stop (MTA route #4) directly outside.  It runs from 1-3 times per hour, depending on the day of the week.  Uber is highly recommended in Nashville.  They are inexpensive and there are drivers close by nearly always.  Be ready to go when you request your ride!
access: Guests have free use of the first floor of the house as described above.
interaction: This can vary widely depending on my work schedule and how much interaction you want!  If you'd like a trivia partner, a guide to walk with you to Five Points, or someone to cook a meal with at home, I'm usually up for it!  At other times guests have gone their entire stay and we've not even seen each other.  I am more than willing to provide advice and recommendations, and you can always get in touch with me if needed.  :)
house_rules: No smoking in the home at any time.  Also no use of any open flames.  No heating elements except for those already provided or basic bathroom appliances (hair dryer, curling iron, etc). Naturally, we expect basic respect for the home and property.  If any significant damage occurs or excessive cleaning is required we will claim through Airbnb who may pursue offending guests for reimbursement.
host_about:
Hi there! I'm Melissa. 

As of August 2016...I've taken over management for this this lovely East Nashville home on behalf of Paul (the homeowner). I'm happy to answer any/all questions you may have about this property or Nashville before/after/during your visit. 

I've lived in Tennessee since I was the age of four and I've called different areas of East Nashville home for the last four years. I work full time in kitchen and bath design with a little architectural photography as well. I love to camp, kayak, garden, travel, and appreciate a good brunch on the weekends. :)

The villa itself is peaceful but the vibrant town of Calvia is just one kilometer away, meaning guests can enjoy the numerous restaurants, bars, services and amenities that the town offers. The nearby villages of Palmanova, Santa Ponsa and Port Adriano also offer a range of different dining options, from traditional Spanish taverns to more modern cuisine. The nearest beach is just a short drive away and offers clean sands and safe waters for swimming. The nearby Serra de Tramuntana mountain range offers ample opportunity for walking, cycling and exploring, making it ideal for nature lovers.

neighborhood_overview: Since its medieval origin, the street of Faubourg Saint Antoine (which connects the Place de la Bastille and the Place de Nation) is the artery of crafts, especially of the cabinetmaking. The Parisians call this area the Faidherbe Village because it is probably one of the most friendly and vivid area of Paris, where you can find lots of restaurants (some of them are very famous) and bars. The emulation is in, and around, a golden triangle between the subway stations Ledru-Rolin, and Faidherbe-Chaligny Charonne. Whether gourmet, traditional or international that’s where you can find lots of friendly and not too expensive addresses. You'll also find many shops and handcrafts boutiques, squares for picnics, etc. The famous Aligre market (one of the best and oldest market in Paris) and its building classified as historical monuments is a few minutes’ walk and it offers a tasty destination every morning except Monday. There are also many supermarkets in the area, including one right beside
notes: Soirée ou fête privée n'est pas acceptable.  Private party is not acceptable.
transit: The apartment is on the line 8, Faidherbe-Chaligny station or line 1 Reuilly-Diderot station (5 minutes) or the 1,2,6,9 and RER line A to Nation (8 minutes). The area is so well connected that you almost never need to change the ligne to get to any tourist place: • Line 8 passes the following stations : Bastillem Winter Circus, République, Les Grands Boulevards, Opéra, Madeleine, Concorde, Invalides, Ecole Militaire (Champ de Mars and Eiffel Tower) ... • Line 1 (station Reuilly-Diderot) takes you from le chateau de Vincennes (Floral Park) to la Defense via the Gare de Lyon, Bastille, Saint Paul (Marais), hotel de ville, Châtelet, the Louvre, Les Tuileries, Concorde, Champs Elysees, Arc de Triomphe - Etoile, and Jardin d'acclimatation ... Place de la Nation is a hub for the Paris Metro. • Line 2 serves the north of Paris: Père Lachaise, Belleville, Pigalle, Anvers (Montmartre), Blanche (Moulin Rouge), Parc Monceau ... • Line 6 gives access to the southern districts: Bercy, Place d'Itali

name: Precious Villa Gran Llombards
summary: A stay at Gran Llombards is absolutely perfect for families looking for a peaceful stay in one of best preserved areas of Mallorca and sample, first hand, the delights of this beautiful island.
space: Made from traditional Mallorquín stone, the house has four large double bedrooms, each with their own bathroom. The two bedrooms overlooking the garden and spa swimming pool also have access to a large balcony with views out over the countryside. Downstairs the house has a large reception hall leading into a double sized sitting room, dining room and finally fully complete kitchen. Outside there is a large terrace with seating for 6 and a relaxed area. The spa swimming pool is perfect for young children and boasts a Jacuzzi setting. There are also sun loungers and a sofa in the small chillout zone. There is room to park two cars and children can explore freely without parents worrying as the house has large electric wooden gates.   Bigger groups can also rent Es Llombards, which is situated next door.

neighborhood_overview: The sister property of Es Llombards, Gran Llombards is a carefully restored Mallorquín farmhouse situated in the quaint little village of Es Llombards, in the south east corner of Mallorca, just a 20 minute drive from Es Trenc, one of the best beachs in Europe and 10 minutes away from the closest little coves. Es Llombards has a number of local bars and restaurants where you can relax outside and watch the world go by. Opposite the house there is a small play area for children and padel courts for hire. The village of Ses Salines is only a 7 minute drive away and has some of the chicest restaurants in the area and a large supermarket and those looking for a larger traditional Mallorcan town only need to drive 7 minutes in the opposite direction to find Santanyí; well-known for its lively market on a Wednesday and Friday and its art galleries.
access: Amenities: Near the Sea, Internet, Pool, Telephone, TV, Music Sound-System, Central Heating, Refrigerator, Fridge, Dishwasher, Pro Coffee Maker, Oven, Microwave, Alarm, Outdoor Furniture, Table Tenis, Optional parking.
interaction: Included in price -Housekeeping (one time a week) -Pool Cleaner -Gardener -Taxes
host_about:
At Villa Club we aim to provide the very best in hospitality and service throughout Spain. We warmly welcome you to stay at one of our beautiful Villas and invite you to relax pool side or to enjoy some of the best foods and sights that Spain has to offer.

Each Villa offers a comfortable and welcoming home away from home in some of the most sought after locations in the Balearic Islands, Andalusia and Catalonia. Each Villa comes fully-equipped with everything you may need during for you to enjoy your holidays.

We have Villas to suit everyone’s tastes including modern seaside homes and historic residences in the Spanish countryside.

Please contact us if you require further info about our villas, we are always happy to help!

name: Beautiful House, Convenient Location
summary: Cool and comfortable renovated craftsman cottage!  High ceilings, wood floors, crown molding, spacious kitchen, relaxing porch, and 5 mins to downtown, 5 minutes to Five Points.
space: Beautifully renovated 1920 Craftsman cottage fully redone in 2009.  Tall ceilings, massive crown molding, exposed brick, and beautiful woodwork throughout the house make it a great place to relax or to host your friends.  The front porch has a nice shaded sitting area facing the neighborhood. The downstairs full bath includes a clawfoot tub with a shower ring and hand-held shower head.  The half bath is off of the living room and can accommodate someone while the main bath is in use.  The upstairs master bath has a giant whirlpool tub, dual sinks, a dressing area, and a separate tiled shower.   The kitchen is fully equipped: gas range with cast iron griddle, dual gas oven, microwave oven, and a modern fridge/freezer.  Cookware, utensils, and dishes are available.  Front loading washer and dryer for you to use. If you have any other questions about the home, please do ask!
description: Cool and comfortable renovated craftsman cottage!  High ceilings, wood floors, crown molding, spacious kitchen, relaxing porch, and 5 mins to downtown, 5 minutes to Five Points. The front porch has a nice shaded sitting area facing the neighborhood. The downstairs full bath includes a clawfoot tub with a shower ring and hand-held shower head.  The half bath is off of the living room and can accommodate someone while the main bath is in use.  The upstairs master bath has a giant whirlpool tub, dual sinks, a dressing area, and a separate tiled shower.   The kitchen is fully equipped: gas range with cast iron griddle, dual gas oven, microwave oven, and a modern fridge/freezer.  Cookware, utensils, and dishes are available.  Front loading washer and dryer for you to use.
neighborhood_overview: East Nashville has been the hippest neighborhood for years and continues to develop in exciting ways!  The home is smack in between a Brooklyn-style hipster scene on one side and the downtown Nashville Broadway honky-tonk country scene on the other!  Walking downtown or to any of the blooming East Nashville business districts is an option, with the center of Five Points, LP Field, and 1st and Broadway all less than a mile away.   Sky Blue Cafe, Yeast Nashville Bakery, and the Crying Wolf are each only a few blocks, respectively featuring great breakfast and lunch, a great bakery and coffee, and a hip bar with the best burgers in Nashville.
notes: My home welcomes pets; therefore, it is not advised for guests with severe cat or dog allergies. Security Deposit will not be charged unless a claim is made within 48hrs of your departure.
transit: There is a bus stop (MTA route #4) directly outside.  It runs from 1-3 times per hour, depending on the day of the week.  Uber and Lyft are highly recommended in Nashville.  They are inexpensive and there are drivers close by nearly always.  Be ready to go when you request your ride!
access: Guests will have access to the entire home minus the upstairs closet.  3 bedrooms, 4 beds, 3.5 baths, living area, laundry, backyard, and kitchen.
house_rules: No smoking in the home at any time, as well as no use of any open flames or heating elements except for those already provided or basic bathroom appliances (hair dryer, curling iron, etc). We expect basic respect for the home and property.  Any damage or excessive cleaning required after a stay will be recovered from the deposit funds and claimed through Airbnb.  Airbnb may pursue offending guests for damage exceeding the deposit. Upstairs loft will comfortably fit 2-3 queen/full size air mattresses for more guests (mattresses & bedding not provided). Added fee per guest after the first 8. Extra guests MUST be approved by host.
host_about:
Hi there! I'm Melissa. 

As of August 2016...I've taken over management for this this lovely East Nashville home on behalf of Paul (the homeowner). I'm happy to answer any/all questions you may have about this property or Nashville before/after/during your visit. 

I've lived in Tennessee since I was the age of four and I've called different areas of East Nashville home for the last four years. I work full time in kitchen and bath design with a little architectural photography as well. I love to camp, kayak, garden, travel, and appreciate a good brunch on the weekends. :)

summary: Guest bedroom in a renovated craftsman cottage in the Historic Edgefield neighborhood of East Nashville, close to both downtown and Five Points.  Keyed door to lock your possessions.
space: This bedroom is downstairs among high ceilings, beautiful molding and woodwork, and exposed century-old brick chimneys. The kitchen is fully equipped: gas range with cast iron griddle, dual gas oven, microwave oven, and a modern fridge/freezer.  Cookware, utensils, and dishes are available.  There is a modern nice washer and dryer for your use in the laundry room on the side of the kitchen.  We have two sweet tuxedo cats that mostly stay outdoors but occasionally run inside, and we adopted a super sweet, dorky puppy that mostly stays upstairs with me or in the backyard.  It's a cute crew! Listing price is for 2 guests.  We can accept up to three if you'd like to use an air mattress (or arrange to use the living room couch). If you have any other questions about the home, please do ask!

If you have any other questions about the home, please do ask! Guests have free use
neighborhood_overview: The house is a comfortable 1 mile walk across the scenic Shelby Street pedestrian bridge to downtown and less than a mile to Five Points, the heart of the East Nashville business district featuring 3 Crow Bar, The 5 Spot, and Margot Cafe.  Even closer are Sky Blue Cafe for a great local breakfast or good coffee, and The Crying Wolf, a hip new bar with great simple cocktails and amazing burgers.
notes: We have two tuxedo cats and a puppy, they're very sweet and really not a problem for anyone with MILD allergies since they mostly stay outside or upstairs with me. Also, we allow guests with pets to stay as long as they play nice!  The house is very clean, however probably not the best choice for anyone with severe cat or dog allergies.
transit: There is a bus stop (MTA route #4) directly outside.  It runs from 1-3 times per hour, depending on the day of the week.  Uber is highly recommended in Nashville.  They are inexpensive and there are drivers close by nearly always.  Be ready to go when you request your ride!
access: Guests have free use of the first floor of the house as described above.
interaction: This can vary widely depending on my work schedule and how much interaction you want!  If you'd like a trivia partner, a guide to walk with you to Five Points, or someone to cook a meal with at home, I'm usually up for it!  At other times guests have gone their entire stay and we've not even seen each other.  I am more than willing to provide advice and recommendations, and you can always get in touch with me if needed.  :)
house_rules: No smoking in the home at any time, outside is fine.  No use of any open flames. No heating elements except for those already provided or basic bathroom appliances (hair dryer, curling iron, etc). Naturally, we expect basic respect for the home and property.  If any significant damage occurs or excessive cleaning is required we will claim through Airbnb who may pursue offending guests for reimbursement.
host_about:
Hi there! I'm Melissa. 

As of August 2016...I've taken over management for this this lovely East Nashville home on behalf of Paul (the homeowner). I'm happy to answer any/all questions you may have about this property or Nashville before/after/during your visit. 

I've lived in Tennessee since I was the age of four and I've called different areas of East Nashville home for the last four years. I work full time in kitchen and bath design with a little architectural photography as well. I love to camp, kayak, garden, travel, and appreciate a good brunch on the weekends. :)

name: Can Sanchez
summary: Finca Ca'n Sánchez is built with first class materials including much fine woodwork thoughout the house and decorated to a very high standard.
space: DESCRIPTION Finca Ca'n Sánchez is built with first class materials including much fine woodwork thoughout the house and decorated to a very high standard. The house has four double rooms on two floors. There is an excellent fully equipped kitchen, a large and light living room, double bedroom and a bathroom. From the wide hall way, stairs lead up to the first floor where there are two double bedrooms sharing another bathroom and a large double bedroom with bathroom en suite which has also a whirlpool tub.  Surrouded by its gardens to the front of the house is an extensive area for ample parking. To the front of the house there is a 9m x 5m pool equipped with deckchairs, umbrellas and other pool furniture. The terrace area makes a great place to dine by moonlight. There is a stone building with a barbecue/pool bathroom. name: 2BR/2BTH in St Lazare
summary: This bright, sunny, air-conditioned apartment is located on the border of the 8th  and 9th arrondissements. Calm and cozy, it is on the top floor of the building,  meaning that it remains silent.
space: This 85 sqm apartment is located on the border of the 8th  and 9th arrondissements. Very secured and equipped with a lift, it's a typical parisian apartment dating of the 19th century. The lift or the stairs will take you right to this beautiful apartment. The newly refurbished kitchen, located just off of the entrance, is fully equipped with modern, stainless steel appliances and in particular a dish washer and a dryer. The living room contains a sofa, arm chairs, and a cable television.  The two bedrooms are located to the left of the living room. One has two twin beds, the other, a queen-sized bed. There are two modern bathrooms, one with a shower, and one with a bathtub. Both also have toilets and large porcelain sinks.  The top-floor views are truly splendid, and let in lots of light. Each window in the living room and bedrooms also opens up to a small balcony.

space: Very nice apartment of 40m2 in a typically Parisian neighborhood offers access to a number of main attractions of the capital. Have a good stay in our french Capital!

neighborhood_overview: In the foothills of the Serra de Tramuntana, the property is found in one of the wildest and least known parts of Mallorca, and is full of natural hideouts and secret coves that visitors can explore. The nearby village of Banyalbufar is a must-visit for guests. Situated on the coast at the south-west of the Tramuntana mountains, it dates back to the 10th Century, and is home to a number of interesting architectural sites, including the lovely Nativitat de Maria Church. Port des Canonge is a small residential district in Banyalbufar’s municipal area, and has steadily grown over the last fifty years to include a number of lovely holiday homes and luxury villas.

name: Luxury and comfort at Es Llombards
summary: Bright and spacious, this stylish and discrete villa is a wonderful option for guests looking for some rest and relaxation during their time in Mallorca.
space: Situated on the peaceful south-east corner of Mallorca, on the edge of the tiny village of Es Llombards, this basic, but yet very comfortable, villa offers guests a tranquil base during their time on this beautiful island. Set in spacious gardens, the three bedroom villa is predominantly open-plan in design. The large living, kitchen and dining area is located at the back of the house, and the French-style windows that run along one side open out onto the beautiful terrace and gardens. Complete with a stylish shaded outdoor dining area, the spacious patio is linked to the large swimming pool via a paved walkway. Each of the three double bedrooms has have been tastefully and thoughtfully decorated in keeping with the clean lines and classic elegance evident throughout the rest of the house. The large master bedroom comes complete with a designer en-suite bathroom, whilst the two twin bedrooms share the second bathroom.

neighborhood_overview: Little Italy means fantastic food in any city. There is an affordable traditional Napolitano pizza place just a few doors down that is known throughout North America. I have been to 33 countries and this pizza is unbelievable. Great coffee and pastries in the morning especially thanks to the areas Portuguese community that is in fact as numerous and obvious as the Italian one. It's a Little Lisbon too! Do NOT leave without trying fresh 'pasteis de Nata" in any of the popular Portuguese bakeries.
notes: I am a fiercely tolerant and non-judgmental man in all areas of my life. Mutual respect is my mantra. Hosting guests in my home is a true pleasure.
transit: FREE PARKING DIRECTLY AT FRONT DOOR IN THE EVENING Streetcar directly out front. Trip to the nearest subway/metro station is 10-15min. Abundance of taxis and Uber around.

house_rules: NO smoking inside. You can smoke cigarettes and marijuana OUTSIDE. Kindly take off your shoes when entering the apartment. There is a shoe rack by the door to use if you wish.  No alcohol consumption or butts directly in front of the property. If you wish to have a drink please let me dispose of your empty can or bottle. Loud music and yelling/screaming in common areas will NOT be tolerated.  Respect our neighbours. Guests will receive one polite warning if they are disturbing others. There's no 2nd warning. I'm a super nice guy though :)
host_about:
I am a first-generation Canadian born and raised in downtown Toronto. My multicultural and multilingual parents are avid travelers who, along with my realtives across the pond, showed me a great deal of the world both literally and culturally before I even turned 18. As an adult I carried on the familial wanderlust and have now set foot inside 33 sovereign nations and about a dozen dependant territories. I have also, for a much more significant amout of time, resided in France and Ireland. I hold passports for the four sovereign nation of Canada, UK, Ireland, and Romania. Believe it or not! I am a quadruple citizen.

I sincerely look forward to sharing my love of travel and sharing knowledge with you. My hosting 'style' can definitely be personable and involved. That being said I respect privacy above all else.

 This includes with fellow Canadians for whom I hope to be a suitable ambassador to my wonderful birthplace, which has grown into a truly alpha global city; having moved ahead by leaps and bounds since my own 'first visit' in the late 80s.

So to everyone planning a visit I say in the languages used by members of my own extended family:

Welcome!
Céad míle fáilte!
Bienvenue!
Croeso!
Bine ati venit!

Regards,

Aodhan Wolfe Dickson

neighborhood_overview: There is something so charming about the East Village. It still has that old New York feel, with tenement buildings, small parks (Thompkin Square Park is a block away), historic buildings and classic eateries. There is something for everyone in the east village but it caters to a sort of "low profile" person who may be wearing designer one of a kind pieces mixed with awesome vintage finds. Sipping an Abraço Cortado on the corner of 7th and 1st Ave.  So if fine dinning, speak easy bars, eclectic cuisine, Turkish bath houses (there is one across the street), Pilates/yoga in classic 1890's style buildings is up your alley then come stay in the East Village. Plus you'll be walking distance to all things Posh in SoHo, all things Quaint in the West Village, all things indie in the Lower East Side, all things Italian in little Italy and all things Asian in Chinatown. You'll have it all at your finger tips! Enjoy!
notes: Please please please do not loose the keys. They cost a lot of money to replace because they can only be duplicated by one company and because they have a special fob on them which is also considerably expensive. Thank you!
transit: 4 blocks from the L train (two stops from Union Square with connects to just about every train in Manhattan), few blocks away from the 6 Train, 10 blocks from the F train.  And walking distance to all the amazing wonders of Downtown Manhattan!
access: Outdoor patio, and apartment :-)
house_rules: No Smoking. Respectful of neighbors. No parties.  No pets. Take shoes off when in apartment.  Do not forget your keys.  Please do not buzz all apartments if you get locked out to get into the building. Please call me if you need anything! No I will not be coming into the apartment while you are staying there.
host_location: New York, New York, United States
host_about: I moved from Los Angeles to New York and worked in the fashion industry for 3 amazing years.  After a fabulous and exhausting time I decided to take off to Thailand to Study Yoga, my true passion.  I had been practicing for 7 years and it was in Thailand that I recieved my 200 hour Yoga Instructor Certification! I'm more proud of this 2 month intensive study than my entire college education at UCSB.  After thailand I traveled to Lao, England, Scottland, Wales, Ireland, Neitherlands, and Spain before flying to Switzerland to take a chance on love and visit the one man I shared a flirtatious evening with in the north of Thailand.  A few days turned into 3 months and now I live between Los Angeles, New York and Switzerland teaching yoga and sharing my love of travel, yoga, and the whimsical idea that love CAN/DOES happen anywhere/everywhere.  Hope you will enjoy my apartment as much as I did while I was in NYC!  I have an excellent team helping me maintain the apartment and if you need anything I am always here for you! Namaste! And all the Best! Rachel

name: Garden Cottage in the Heart of SC!
summary: Come stay in this modern and cozy cottage in the heart of Santa Cruz!  During the day, enjoy a short walk to surfing, beach, boardwalk, wharf, and downtown.  Then come relax on your deck amongst the fruit trees!
space: ***Please note we collect the 11% Transient Occupancy Tax.  This tax is included in the price Come relax in this open floor plan (there is no door between the bedroom and living room), one bedroom, one bath cottage.   In the morning, grab a cup of complementary coffee or tea and enjoy it on the sunny deck.  Make yourself at home with a fridge, microwave, and coffee machine (no sink or stove). The large and sunny bedroom has all new furniture, queen bed, large walk-in closet, and looks out onto the deck. Hang out in the living room on the comfy futon (which folds out into a bed) and watch free Netflix, Amazon Prime, and HBO GO on the LCD TV with Roku player (no cable tv or satellite). Free wi-fi access :)  Or, grab a book from the bookcase or a board game. Towels, sheets, pillows, and comforters for the bed and the futon provided.  Travel crib available upon request. One parking pass provided for on-street parking.

neighborhood_overview: Our cottage is in (we think!) the perfect location to enjoy all that Santa Cruz has to offer - we're only blocks from downtown, the boardwalk, the wharf, and Cowell's beach.  You can walk to the beach for coffee and breakfast at the Picnic Basket in the morning, bask in the sun on the deck in the cottage in the afternoon, and then walk downtown for dinner at night. Also, the walking path and pontoon path in Neary Lagoon is a hidden treasure, with all sorts of beautiful wildlife.
notes: Like many other popular rentals, we have been contacted by the city to collect a transient occupancy tax of 11% of the total cost (before AirBNB fees). I'm sure all rentals will be collecting this very soon (all hotels currently collect it) - help us in being compliant with the law :).  The tax is included in the price and breaks down as follows: Summer weekday price: (phone number hidden) Summer weekend price: (phone number hidden) Winter weekday price:(phone number hidden) Winter weekend price: (phone number hidden) Cleaning fee: 30 + 11% = 33 Each additional person per night over 2 people: 10 + 11% = 11 We are very pleased to share our living space with you.  Occasionally, our very friendly medium-sized dog, Kona, pays a visit and roams the yard.  Please be sure you are comfortable with this! Two night minimum if staying Saturday night (i.e. Friday and Saturday or Saturday and Sunday).
host_about:
Hi!  My husband and I are very excited to be sharing our living space with you!  We love living in Santa Cruz - there is so much to do and it is such a beautiful place to live.  

We love hiking, rock climbing, skiing, surfing (my husband), and spending time with friends and family.  We are looking forward to meeting new and interesting people and showing you the best of Santa Cruz!
street: Neary St, Santa Cruz, CA 95060, United States

host_about:
I am a first-generation Canadian born and raised in downtown Toronto. My multicultural and multilingual parents are avid travelers who, along with my realtives across the pond, showed me a great deal of the world both literally and culturally before I even turned 18. As an adult I carried on the familial wanderlust and have now set foot inside 33 sovereign nations and about a dozen dependant territories. I have also, for a much more significant amout of time, resided in France and Ireland. I hold passports for the four sovereign nation of Canada, UK, Ireland, and Romania. Believe it or not! I am a quadruple citizen.

I sincerely look forward to sharing my love of travel and sharing knowledge with you. My hosting 'style' can definitely be personable and involved. That being said I respect privacy above all else.

 This includes with fellow Canadians for whom I hope to be a suitable ambassador to my wonderful birthplace, which has grown into a truly alpha global city; having moved ahead by leaps and bounds since my own 'first visit' in the late 80s.

So to everyone planning a visit I say in the languages used by members of my own extended family:

Welcome!
Céad míle fáilte!
Bienvenue!
Croeso!
Bine ati venit!

Regards,

Aodhan Wolfe Dickson
street: Downtown Toronto, Toronto, ON M5T 1E8, Canada

interaction: Bien sur, je serais ravie de partager avec vous mes conseils ou bonnes adresses si vous me le demandez.
house_rules: - L'accès a la piscine commune sur le toit de l'immeuble est autorisé seulement pendant la saison d'été - Nous avons un chat; donc je vous déconseille de réserver sans vous assurez qu'aucun des voyageurs ne soit allergique :) - Vous ne serez pas seuls dans le logement, donc il est important de respecter mes colocataires, ainsi que la propreté des parties communes que vous utiliserez - L'appartement étant dans une copropriété, les parties communes de l'immeuble également doivent être respectées
host_about:
Bonjour,
Je suis française et vis à Barcelone depuis plus d'un an maintenant;
Cette ville m'a très rapidement séduite; multiculturelle, les habitants sont détendus et sympathiques et comment ne pas l'être avec le temps clément et le soleil toute l'année :D
Je suis une personne joviale et dynamique, j'aime échanger avec les personnes de différentes cultures et apprendre évidemment!
Je parle français, anglais et allemand, et mon niveau d'espagnol est correct (je comprends plus que je ne le parle)
Personnellement il est très important pour moi de me sentir bien chez moi, et je m'appliquerais également à ce que vous vous sentiez chez vous, chez moi :)
Au plaisir de faire votre rencontre

name: 2 room Apartment Schöneberg

neighborhood_overview: The area known as les Halles was once the market district of Paris, its 'stomach', as writer Emile Zola called it in 1873. Today the covered marketplace has been replaced by an underground transport hub, but the area remains a bustling, dynamic organ of Parisian life. In addition to the boutiques, restaurants and cafes lining the streets, there are many outdoor markets. The center of the capital, every attraction, train station, and airport is easily accessible from les halles .
